The paper proposes an end-to-end convolutional neural network framework for medical image registration, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of unsupervised learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.AI another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of additional data to improve performance, which involves information theory (IT) concepts, making cs.IT a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses neural networks for registration, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (NE), making cs.NE a possible sub-category as well.
